animal.description:
Hi, my name is Khaleesi! I go by Peanut too.

I was surrendered to the rescue because my mom got sick and was no longer able to take care of me. She loved me so so much though! Now I am looking for a new forever home where I will be loved just as much as I was in my first home.

I’m a firecracker, frisky, zealous, lively, and high spirited! I really enjoy playing, and would love to entertain you with my antics! Exercise keeps me happy and content, without it I can get a little worked up. I do best when I have had a chance to get my energy out so that I can be calm later. Going for walks, engaging in play and doing outdoor activities with my new family daily would make me very happy!

I would make a great playmate but would also love to join you on the couch, I’m happy either way! I can’t think of anything better than getting love and attention from my family! Affection is my middle name! When its chill time, forget the couch or the bed, lying in your cozy lap would make me happiest! Nothing would make me happier than to find a family to devote myself to! You won’t find a more dedicated, loving companion!

While I do get along with people I know, due to my size / age / personality I would do best in a home without young children. I also need to be an only pet. Though I can tolerate being around a select few, I don’t play well with other dogs or cats. I really just need to be the center of your world!

I adore snuggling! But I don’t share my cuddles with just anyone, I prefer to get to know you a bit first! It takes me a little bit of time to become comfortable with new people so please allow me a bit of time to warm up to you, trust me, you won't regret it. Once I know I am home I will do my famous 'wiggle butt jumps' for you to show you how happy I am!

If you think we may be a good match, or you would like to get to know me better, please click the Adoption Application button below my profile on the rescue website and you will be contacted by an adoption counselor!  Here is the link > https://www.smallbreedrescue.org/Animal/AnimalDetails/162

Due to home introductions that are part of the adoption process, we can only accept applications for interested parties who are in or near San Diego County, California at this time.

PLEASE READ THE ENTIRE BIO BELOW – LINCOLN HAS VERY SPECIFIC NEEDS.
POTENTIAL ADOPTERS MUST BE LOCAL TO CLEVELAND OHIO WITHIN 1 HOUR OR LESS.
Lincoln is a 3-year-old Boxer who came to us because his former family had some concerns regarding his behavior. Lincoln completed a four-week stay & train and is now settling in at his foster home. While he was in training, he worked on socialization and obedience.
Although he has shown improvement and can behave appropriately with other dogs, we are looking for a home that does NOT have any other pets. Lincoln has some prey drive and resource guarding and will do best being the only animal in his new home. He will require a home with structure, consistency, and large breed dog experience.
Potential adopters must be local to Cleveland, Ohio (within 1 hour or less) to utilize continued training support. We are also requiring a fully fenced in yard and no children visiting often or living in the home (children 14 years and older are okay depending on their energy level).
Lincoln is crate trained and house broken.  He is a really fun and playful guy who has a lot of love and kisses to spare. He enjoys taking walks and is great on a leash.  He loves toys and treats too! If you meet the requirements above, please complete an adoption application for approval to determine if Lincoln would be a great fit for your home.

birthday: 10/15/2017

age: 3 years

adoption fee: $400

animal.description:
Meet Whiskey! 

This handsome boy is a 3 year old yellow lab mix who ready to find his forever home! 

Reacently completing his Heartworm treatment in the late fall this handsome boy is full of life! He loves his toys especially his tennis balls and stuffed animals.

He is very sweet and gentle around kids. 
Good with other dogs that The foster family has had him around but they are sure about cats as they don’t have any. 

* We do not have the availability to cat test him *

Whiskey LOVES to cuddle and go for long walks. He does well on leash and great in his crate when he can see you. He does not however do well in the crate when he’s left alone or out of sight from you.  Whiskey does have some separation anxiety which he has recently been to the vet to have evaluated and the fosters have been trying to work him through it but he will still need some work. 

We highly recommend a dog savy home where Whiskey will not be left alone for long hours of the day. We also recommend that the new home have some experience handling separation anxiety or are willing to put the work in to discuss curbing it with their vet or a trainer. 

We also recommend that he not be the only dog in the home or if he is that the new adopted owner or family would be willing to put in the extra work as far as socialization and both mental and physical exercise.

Adoption fee: $350

Presently in foster near Brick, NJ

If interested please apply at CompassRoseRescue.org

Adoption fee $350 

LAP NEEDED!  Sadie Belle is almost fifteen years old Maltese.  She tips the scale at 2.6 lbs.  
Sadie Belle is healthy with no medical issues.  On cold days she is a little slower jumping out of bed but what senior lady doesn’t?

Sadie Belle will sit on your lap or beside you as long as you can give ear rubs.  She can also be “little miss independent” and spend time alone in her bed.  Sadie Belle exercises by exploring the house.  On sunny days, she likes to spend a short, supervised time in the yard.  She is house trained to pee pads.

Sadie Belle has no teeth but it does not keep her from eating her kibble.  She also likes tiny puppy cookies.

Sadie Belle is spayed.  She is heart worm negative and on a preventative.  She is current on all her vaccinations and is microchipped.

Sadie gets along well with other dogs.  She is not appropriate for a home with young children.  Sadie would be perfect for a senior. 

Adoption fee $350
** The Texas Comptroller now requires sales tax on adoption fees.

** Temporarily Suspended due to COVID **
Monthly Meet & Greets  (12:00 - 2:00)
Petco (in Leander) every 1st Saturday of the month
Pet Supplies Plus (Parmer & Mopac) every third Saturday of the month


** Please note: Due to their size, our dogs are not suitable for homes with children under 5..

We do not have a facility, all dogs are fostered in the homes of our volunteers. If you are interested in adopting a dog from Lil' Paws Maltese Rescue and other Petite Paws, please visit our website at www.lilpaws-malteserescue.org and fill out an adoption application. This is the first step in our adoption process. Our goal is to place our dogs in safe, stable and loving homes in the Austin Metropolitan area. Thanks for looking!

Lil' Paws Maltese Rescue and other Petite Paws depends on donations to keep the dogs in our program healthy. Many health issues are taken care of before a dog leaves a rescue: spaying, neutering, immunizations, dental care, and in some cases major surgery. Because of the cost of this care, donations are essential to enable us to continue our work. If you would like to show appreciation for what we do and help us continue to do it please go to our website homepage and click the donate button. We thank you in advance for your support.

animal.description:
PLEASE NOTE- AN APPLICATION FROM THE WEBSITE ALMOSTHOMEDOGS.ORG IS REQUIRED PRIOR TO ANY MEET AND GREETS.  CALLING, EMAILING, AND USING THE "CONTACT US" LINK ON PETFINDER ARE NOT USEFUL. WE MAY BE TOO BUSY TO ANSWER ANY INQUIRES.

Rose and siblings were found in Texas, dumped in a field in freezing weather, found by a good samaritan, and rescued to Maryland.  Sweet and playful, currently about 10 weeks old, about 8 pounds (expected to be about 35-40 pound dogs).  They are probably part terrier/part pit bull, part something else but 100 percent adorable.


APPLY AT ALMOSTHOMEDOGS.ORG

The adoption fee for puppies less than 6 months old is $350, which includes the cost of routine vetting, including age appropriate vaccinations, worming, flea/tick preventative and spay/neuter. Puppies under 4 months of age may go to adoptive homes before they are spayed/neutered. Adopters who choose to adopt a puppy that has not yet been spayed/neutered are subject to an additional deposit of $100 (refundable upon proof of spay/neuter.) Included in the adoption fee, the rescue will arrange spay/neuter by a partner vet at a predetermined appointment when the puppy is between 4-6 months of age. It is the responsibility of the adopter to bring the adopted puppy back to the rescue vet for spaying/neutering or to send verification from their own vet that the puppy had been spayed/neutered.  All of our dogs will be microchipped.

Because our dogs are in foster homes, applications are required prior to setting up any appointments. Calling or emailing may delay your consideration. Find our application on our website, almosthomedogs.org, then click on "Adopt" tab at top

We are a non profit no kill 501 (c)3 rescue. Please understand that we do our best to describe our dogs but often we rescue them with virtually no information about them and often our best educated guess can be challenging. Currently check, cash or venmo is preferred payment.

animal.description:
****Thank you for your interest in Chewy.  At this time we are not taking any more applications for him as we have over 60 at the moment.
We will remove this notice if we open applications again.  Thank you for your understanding****





Hi my name is Chewy! Well, this is the name that I like and respond to best :)

I was surrendered to the rescue by my previous owner and I am now looking for my true forever home.

I’m happy go lucky, carefree, engaging, adaptive, and cheerful. I like to take my time approaching new situations. While I am a bit shy with new faces and places, I warm up as I become more familiar with my environment. While I do get along with others, due to my size / age / personality I would do best in a home with no children.

My foster parents have been helping me to learn manners or what we call 'Petiquette'. Sometimes I have trouble controlling my excitement and impulses. I have a tendency to be a bit pushy and can play a little rough with other small dogs but I'm finally figuring it out.

Being a young dog, exercise keeps me happy and content, without it I can get a little worked up. I do best when I have had a chance to get my energy out so that I can be calm later. Going for walks, engaging in play and doing outdoor activities with my new family daily would make me very happy! And when it's time to chillax, forget the couch or the bed, lying in your cozy lap is where I want to be!

I would do well with some additional positive reinforcement training especially socializing with new people. I will require regular grooming and annual vet checks so the more comfortable I am around people, the better these experiences will be for everyone!

If you think we may be a good match, or you would like to get to know me better, please click the Adoption Application button below my profile on the rescue website and you will be contacted by an adoption counselor!  Here is the link > https://www.smallbreedrescue.org/Home/AnimalDetails/176

Due to home introductions that are part of the adoption process, we can only accept applications for interested parties who are in or near San Diego County, California at this time.

animal.description: Hello. My name is Noel. I am a red merle Catahoula Leopard dog mix, and by far and away my favorite thing to do is cuddle. I love to cuddle at night, in the morning, after breakfast, before my walk, after dinner, in the car, and anytime in between. I've learned lots of new tricks, but walking on a leash is still a bit of a challenge, because everything is so interesting! I've made a ton of improvements though and I'm getting better every day. The best is when I get to run free at the dog park and the little dogs let me play with them and chase them around. For some reason, cats and other little furry animals don't like it as much when I chase them. My foster mom says I jump so high that I must be part gazelle, whatever that is. So I need a tall fence to keep me from exploring where I shouldn't. Despite my size, I'm still a puppy and have lots of puppy wiggles to get out, but after that, can we cuddle? My adoption fee is $350. I am up to date on all my shots, spayed and microchipped. I am currently undergoing heartworm treatment, so local adoptions only please. Don't worry about my heart, it's still full of love to give. Fill out an app at www.soca-fbc.org under the adoptable tab.

Tool Box just arrived from a rescue partner in KY. Her foster says: She's a very happy, mellow dog. She loves to sleep at our feet during the day and to sleep her in bed in our room at night. She will whimper to be let outside, but has yet to bark. She's very sweet, great around cats, and kids. We do not have a dog, but probably also very good around calm/trained dogs. Enjoys short walks and walks well on a leash.

Sadly, Tool Box
arrived Heartworm positive so Magnificent Mutts will be treating her. After treatment she will go on to lead a normal happy life. Her only restriction is her adopters will need to keep her activity to

a minimum as he goes through the 30 days rest after Heartworm treatment.

Check back for more information and possible restrictions once she fully settles into foster care.

If you are interested in adoption, please complete the Application to Adopt which you can find on our website (
www.magnificentmutts.org
) No phone calls please. Emails only.

Adoption Donation $300 (cash only)

Adoption Fees*

Adult cats starting at $125, Kittens starting at $165.
Dogs/Puppies starting at $225 minimum

animal.description:
Fia / Female / 8 Years / 59 lbs / Street Mix / North York

Meet Fia! Fia comes to us all the way from Puebla City, Mexico! Fia was found living in shelter that did not have the resources to support its residents. The conditions were very poor and as a senior, Fia was not able to live her golden years like every dog should. Lucky for her she was rescued and flown to Canada in search of a very special family of her own!

Fia is always happy to start a new day and will greet her humans in the morning with a wagging tail. She loves to explore with her nose when she is outside or out for walks. She doesn’t have an interest in toys but she will find any warm blanket to curl up for a nap. She may never be a running or hiking partner, but she makes a loyal companion for slow walks and relaxing at home.

Even though Fia is 8 years young, she has not had the best experience with humans prior to her loving foster home. She can be very timid when new people enter her space and she will avoid eye contact or interacting with them. On walks if strangers pass her closely, she will do what she can to avoid them. After multiple meetings she may chose to come over for a sniff, but petting will be on her terms. Adopters will need to have realistic expectations when meeting her as it will take time earn her trust. She is never aggressive so she may do well with older, dog savvy children that will respect her space as needed.

Fia loves her crate and will settle right away when left alone. She is naturally well mannered in the home and never has accidents. She is currently going for 3-4 walks a day about 20 minutes in duration, but could go longer if it were warmer outside. She is low energy so is overall a low maintenance dog. She walks beautifully on leash and is not reactive to anything.

Fia is an adaptable dog and can thrive in any living environment. She needs patient family that accepts her for her insecurities and can slowly help her through them at her pace. She may never be a dog that loves a high activity household, so a quiet, predictable environment is preferred. She gets along with all dogs as long as they are respectful and don't get in her face. She has not been tested with cats but has no desire to chase small animals.

If you’re interested in adopting Fia please apply at https://www.fetchandreleash.ca/adoption-info#adoption-form

Fia’s adoption fee is $420. To learn more about our adoption fees and the adoption process, please visit our FAQs at https://www.fetchandreleash.ca/about-us#about-faqs.

animal.description:
SAMPSON ~6 years old. Good with kids and dogs. Cats TBD.

GSRA adopts to residents of VA, NC, and SC

Handsome Sampson came to GSRA after living a vagabond life in western NC-he had a home of sorts, but was left on his own to come and go as he pleased, and he received no regular vet care. This means that when he finally landed in the shelter for good (after being a frequent flier for years), he had a few health issues that needed to be addressed-he was absolutely miserable from a long-standing ear infection, and was also heartworm positive. The shelter did a wonderful job of starting to address both problems, but when it became clear that Sampson would need specialty care to really clear his ear infections, they reached out to GSRA to help.

We were happy to offer it! Sampson has been HAPPY to trade his free-wheeling former lifestyle for life as an inside dog with an established routine, regular meals, and soft beds. He's a medium energy guy who enjoys walks (on-leash these days!), car rides, meeting new people and dog friends, and chasing anything you'll throw. But when it's time to just hang out in the house, he's also happy to be your Netflix binge-buddy. He would do fine in a multi-dog household but would also be fine as an only dog, as long as his people were around much of the time. He's also trustworthy left loose in the house while you're away. If its not clear he's pretty much perfect, it should be!!!

Chronic ear infections can take a few months to clear during the best of time, and the covid pandemic is causing most vet clinics (including specialty clinics) to operate with reduced staff. These things combined mean that Sampson won't be truly ready for adoption until March or later. But even if he can't join your family just yet, we thought you'd want to meet him. :-)

For more information on our adoptable pet list please visit: Adoptable Pet List

Please join us at our next Event(s):

Tank is a 5-year-old female blue healer. She was born deaf, but knows many
hand signals and is very smart. She is pure affection with her people,
very loyal and attached. She will do best as the only dog in a home, as
she needs a lot of belly rubs all to herself. When given a proper
introduction with other dogs, she does very well going on walks and hikes

other shelter pups and she does great. However, she did not do well with
the other female blue healer in her previous home, who was a bit of an
aggressor and would often startle Tank, and if she slipped out of the
house unattended, we are told that she can get overexcited when
encountering other dogs and that can lead to problems. But if kept on a
leash and given a calm and secure environment, she has only done well in
our care. She is very strong, but well mostly well mannered on a leash.

Claire Hanson
Blue Mountain Humane Association

Hi there! My name is Max, short for Maximus Minimus as I have maximum personality in a minimum body. I am a very sweet and cuddly boy who is about 6 years old and weighs about 10lbs. I do have a heart murmur, but the vet says it just needs to be watched to make sure I don’t start having trouble with it. I love to cuddle on laps, and in blankies. I am about 80% house broken and will potty outside as long as my people pay attention to when I get restless and want to go to the door.

I love snuggling down in my foster mom’s or dad’s laps and love attention. I get along well with other dogs and cats, but would prefer a home without children under the age of 12. About the only bad habits I have are wanting to be left alone when eating or when I am sound asleep buried in my blankie.

If you are looking for a little buddy who will be your lap snuggler and companion… I am your boy. Won’t you consider making me your furever friend? I will give you all the love and snuggles you could want if you do.

Sincerely, Max

Max is being fostered in Miamisburg by Tracy.

animal.description:
Hi, my name is Indy and I’m ready to find a forever home to call my own. Back in October, I was found all alone while giving birth in the middle of the woods. My babies and I were brought to a shelter where we remained until Take Paws Rescue broke us out. My five little ones and I went into a foster home where we were showered with love. My babies have all been adopted, so now it’s my turn! 

My foster mom says that although I look like a German Shepherd, my personality is, to a t, that of a husky (I can only assume that means huskies have fantastic personalities). I’m full grown at 45 lbs. While there’s no way to know my age for sure, they believe I’m about 3 years old. I’m house broken, kennel trained and even know a couple commands (sit and paw). I love kids and dogs my size, but I would do best in a home with no small animals, including small breed dogs and cats. 

I’m up to date on vaccines and scheduled to be heartworm tested and spayed on 1/25 and 1/27, respectively. 

*Take Paws Rescue saves dogs from high-kill shelters in Southeast Louisiana, owner surrenders, and discarded dogs with uncertain futures. All of our puppies live in foster homes where they are socialized, and well cared for. An application will be required to make sure it’s the perfect match!

 If you are interested in meeting and/or adopting, the first step is to please visit our website to complete an application and read all of our FAQs: https://www.takepawsrescue.org/adopt 

**An inquiry/question on Petfinder is NOT an application. All known details about our animals are posted on their profile and updated daily. Other info would be discussed in detail with the foster during the application review process. Due to the number of inquires received (hundreds daily) we ask you submit an application on our website (a single application can be used for any dog with Take Paws Rescue).

animal.description: Kassie is a 45lb, 6- month old pitty mix. Kassie is a very sweet girl who just loves people and pets. She’s a little shy with other dogs and will stand behind her handler for protection.  We are working on her socialization and building confidence with other dogs. As most pups do, she enjoys playing fetch and tug, going for walks, and spending time with her person. She is crate and kennel trained and knows her sit and place commands, AND is eager to learn more. Right now she has a bad habit of nibbling on you and your clothes when she’s excited so probably be best to not have super small children until we can get this habit broken. Kassie is just a lovely, friendly, spirited little girl who needs to find her FOREVER home. To get more information on a Pups On Parole dog, please contact a representative of the Lassen Humane Society at 530 251-7247 or e-mail ilovepopdogs@yahoo.com.  The Pups On Parole Program started in June of 2007 to help give homeless dogs a second chance at finding an adoptive family.  All dogs in the program spent time in our local county shelter, surrendered by their owners or picked up as strays and waiting for their owners to redeem them or to be adopted by new families.   The selected dogs are brought current on vaccinations, spayed/neutered if necessary, micro chipped, and heart worm tested.  They then are taken to the California Correctional Center Firehouse where they are assigned to a trainer/ inmate fire fighter.  These trainers groom and work with each dog and give them the extra time and attention they need to become wonderful family companions.   Most graduates are house trained and know basic obedience commands.  As of December 2018, 535 dogs have been adopted through this program.  To meet any of the Pups On Parole dogs, arrangements must be made in advance.

animal.description:
I'm Bella, a 10 yr old Siberian Husky. So I'm passed the puppy stage although I still have a lot of energy. I am looking for a retirement home that can spoil me rotten and an owner that can spend lots of time with me. I have lived with kids in the past, but want to be an empty nester now that I am older. I just don't have the patience to handle the youngsters anymore. My foster mom says I'm still pretty energetic for an older woman. I love snuggles, being around my human and running free at the dog park. But don't let me off the leash outside a fenced area because I get so excited about all the smells and forget who you are. I will tell you when I need to go potty (and sometimes I'll just do this because I want outside). I still love to play but can also sleep the day away on your couch. I don't like being left alone for a long time and I don't like the crate (but I can do it). You can trust me to not chew up your furniture if you leave me alone, but I do like to watch the dog channel on TV when I'm home alone. I'd love to find a family who would love me, give me the exercise I need, and cuddle with me at night.

Bella was surrendered at 10 yo due the families financial situation. Bella is dog and cat friendly. She weighs approx. 45lbs. Can you provide her retirement forever?

If you would like to meet Bella, please complete an online application that can be found at: http://hopeanimalrescueofiowa.org/forms/196/dog-application

Adoption fee is $150 which includes spay/neuter, age-appropriate vaccines/tests, and microchip.

during these uncertain times, we are still doing adoptions. To help keep all parties safe we will not be holding adoption events or meetings in any store locations. All meet and greets will be private and held at an outdoor location in Lake Elmo.

Please request an application via email or by a Petfinder request. For more information on the rescue, what the fee includes, surgery program, etc please see the home page.

Adoption fee: $450 cash or card only (There is a $10 fee to use a card) NO CHECKS

Age: 6 months
DOB Approx. 7-23-20?
Gender: Male
Altered: Yes
Breed: Mixed breed
Approx Weight Now: 35 pounds
Approx Weight Grown: 55-70 pounds complete guess as we do not know parents 
Dog-friendly: Yes
Cat-friendly: Yes
Kid-friendly: Yes
House Trained: Yes- as far as we can see but will need a refresher in a new home
Crate-Trained: Yes
Benefit From Formal Training: Will benefit
Energy level: Moderate
History: Adopted as a young puppy and returned

Available for possible foster to adopt

Note From the Foster: 
Hudson is a sweet boy. He loves to snuggle on the couch with you or play ball. He loves playing with our dogs and has been introduced to other dogs that he did well with.  He would benefit from continued training and another dog to play with and socialize with. He does listen fairly well to basic commands. He has done well with our dogs, kids, and cats. Cats he is pretty curious about. He can be jumpy on our 3-year-old child but not the older kids. He accepts social cues from our older dogs fairly well. He walks fairly well on a leash and enjoys being outside. 

He was adopted as a young puppy and returned to us as his family could no longer keep him. We have noticed he is a little apprehensive of new people at our home. Men more than women but after a little time he warms up. We do not push him to greet anyone and request new people in our home to just ignore him until he is ready. This has been working well and the more people he meets the better it gets.

If you would like to foster him to see if he is a good fit before adoption please request a foster application.

animal.description:
Meet Buttercup!

Hi, I'm Buttercup! I'm about 10 years old and 50 pounds. You know, my last family left me when I needed them most. When I realized they weren't coming back for me I sang "why do you build me up (build me up), Buttercup baby, just to let me down", because they kind of let me down. Well, now I'm just so happy to find a family who will be with me through thick and thin. That's right, "I need YOU (I need you), more than anyone darlin', you know that I have from the start"! Okay, enough singing, let's get real here now. I'm just the sweetest thing you'll ever meet! I love to run around my yard and chase my human friends to play with me. I'm such a little doll. Most of my day I love to hang out with my foster mama, bulldozing around in the room as she gets me so excited! Once I'm excited I just spin around in cute circles and chase things around. I do have a lot of energy and I would absolutely love it if I had a yard to play in or could go on walks with my new people. I do like to go in my kennel to eat my breakfast and dinner, that's my favorite time of the day! I am very food motivated! I also will take treats gently from your hand. I get along with older kids who aren't so easy to knock over if I get the zoomies, so no littles under 5. I also get along with cats, but I don't realize how much bigger I am than they are. I love to snuggle up in bed at the end of the day after I got most of my energy out! I'd really love it if I was the only dog, but I do get along with others as long as they aren't too submissive and not super hyper. Sometimes I get so excited I can't control what I do! I just start running and jumping. When I first meet you, I might take a minute to get comfortable. My foster mom thinks I didn't have the best past because I flinch and duck at any sudden movements and loud noises. That's okay though because no matter my past, I'm the most loving dog you will ever meet! I just really hope I can find someone to love my energy and my sweet cuddles at the end of every day. The best of both worlds! Could you be my forever home? I promise, I'll always make you smile.

*Potential adopters with breed experience will take precedence.*

Albert's Dog Lounge is a transporting dog rescue, meaning that we rescue many of our dogs from high kill shelters in areas of dog overpopulation. We are a specialty rescue focusing primarily on senior and special needs dogs.  The vast majority of our dogs come from the Houston, TX area where we have an entire team of volunteers, coordinators, and fosters. We do also work with local shelters, rescues, and owners.  If you apply for a dog that is currently in our local Houston program, we will work to get your dog transported to WI as quickly as possible. We ask that you have patience during this time of uncertainty and unprecedented dog adoptions nationwide. 

Learn more about Albert's Dog Lounge, our mission, and adoption policies by visiting Albertsdoglounge.org. 

Our process includes an approved application, reference checks, a homevisit, and then a meet and greet with the dog. Adoption fee is $275.

Begin your application process by copying this link into your web browser: https://www.albertsdoglounge.org/apply

animal.description:
Brooklyn is a one-year old female, 42 lbs. She came to us as a stray, super sweet, sits nicely, loves people, great with other dogs, actually quite scared of cats.
ADOPTION FEES Dogs & Puppies.....$100.00. This Adoption fee includes: mandatory spay/neuter which will be done before you can take your dog or puppy home with you; basic canine immunizations (DHPP-CPV & Bordatella Intranasal); de-wormings; one-year rabies vaccination if old enough; heartworm test if over five months old; microchip from 24-Pet Watch; certificate for free health examination at your participating veterinarian; and a goodie bag chocked full of information, toys, and more.
The first step to do an adoption is to do our Adoption Application here: https://www.elmorehumane.org/adoption-application-online-form2.html
IMPORTANT - we respond to your emailed applications and queries via email back to you. Please make sure you have either added our email (hselco@bellsouth.net) to your contact list or that you routinely check your SPAM folder for our response just to be safe. If we do not receive a timely response we simply move on to another applicant.
Yes, there are sometimes exceptions to our normal fee for older dogs or special cases. Some of our pets have also been lovingly sponsored by caring people and we will let the approved adopter know about that at the point of adoption. Visit our Website at: http://www.elmorehumane.org The staff would also like to remind you that for faster response to inquiries about adoptable animals to have the animals ID#, name & description. This way your questions will be answered in a timely manner.
All pet adoption websites & our shelter management software require that we choose a primary and/or secondary breed for our dogs. While our staff is quite breed knowledgeable, in many cases we are truly making our best guesses as to their breed(s) based on many factors but cannot promise that what we have said is accurate. So taking into account your own parameters for things such as size, coat care, activity level, etc please come and get to know our dog(s) as individuals to see if their personalities and yours are a forever match.
Phone: (334) 567-3377 Fax: (334) 567-8774 E-mail: hselco@bellsouth.net

animal.description: Emlyn is super sweet and lovable.  She came in as a stray on 1/14/21. Emlyn is estimated to be about 4 years old.  She dances and prances and turns herself into a pretzel for attention. Emlyn most likely belonged to a hunter because she has the letter "B" spray painted on her side. Some of the hunters who have numerous Beagles and Hounds that look much alike spray paint letters or numbers on them in order to identify them later from other hunter's dogs. She must have gotten lost and not retrieved.  Beagles and Hounds that were former hunting dogs still make wonderful pets. They are sweet, loving, goofy and happy for any scrap of food, attention or cozy place to rest. They are usually very tolerant of living conditions, kids and other pets, having been used to so few comforts. Beagles in particular are incredibly sweet. Call (434) 374-8076, or email lakecountryspca@yahoo.com for adoption info. Visit LCSPCA at 11764 Hwy. 15, Clarksville, VA 23927 Mon-Sat. from 12-4 pm.

animal.description:
ADOPT ME ONLINE: https://ophrescue.org/dogs/10368

Hi! 
My name is American Samoa and Im part of the National Parks transport. Im guessed to be a Shepherd mix with hound. My shelter records say Im guessed to be 4 years old, but my foster mom says my energy shows Im not older then 2. She says I play with other dogs and walk on a leash like a puppy. Im working on my basic commands. Im a sweet boy who loves to be scratched and loved on. My favorite time of day is when my foster mom played toys with me in the morning and when Im allowed to run around the back yard with my foster pup siblings! 
Oh!, and of course feeding time! 
I weigh about 65 lbs. I play great with my foster fur friends Male and female. There is a cat here and I understand shes not interested in me. 
 The kids here 12 and 7 think Im adorable and I love on them. I need big time leash training ! I am strong with lots of energy and love to give! Im crate trained and potty .Do you have kids? I love kids! My favorite toys are the ones that squeak! And tennis balls.I cant wait wait to get to my forever home! Is that with you? If so apply today! I wont be available for long!

To adopt this dog, or any OPH dog, fill out the simple online application at https://ophrescue.org 
Operation Paws for Homes, Inc. (OPH) rescues dogs of all breeds and ages from high-kill shelters in NC, VA, MD, and SC, reducing the numbers being euthanized. With limited resources, the shelters are forced to put down 50-90% of the animals that come in the front door. OPH provides pet adoption services to families located in VA, DC, MD, PA and neighboring states. OPH is a 501(c)(3) organization and is 100% donor funded. OPH does not operate a shelter or have a physical location. We rely on foster families who open their homes to give love and attention to each dog before finding a forever home.

animal.description:
BUZBY IS IN A FOSTER HOME

Date of birth: 6/11/2018

1/21/2021:  Buzby is a super cute Beagle/Lab mix!  He’s 2 years old and weighs 60 lbs.  Buzby is a bit shy with new people and new surroundings. Once he knows you, he’s a real sweetheart! His foster family has been working with him to socialize him more and he’s doing better, and with more work and patience in his new home he’ll continue to gain confidence. 

• Buzby lives with big and small dogs and is good with both.  We would like to place him in a home with another dog and with a fenced yard.  He’d really enjoy having a doggie friend in his new home.  We’d ask you to bring your dog in to meet Buzby to see if they could be good buddies.

• Buzby also lives with cats and is good with them.

• He needs a home without young kids, but older kids (teens) would be fine.

• Buzby is easy-going.  He loves to greet his foster family when they come home and he loves to cuddle. He loves car rides and playing in the snow.  He’s not a big barker.

• He is house trained (but may have some accidents initially.)

• Buzby has been neutered, vaccinated, microchipped and tested for heartworms.  

MORE ON ADOPTING OUR DOGS... 

> COVID-19 UPDATE:  PLEASE SUBMIT AN ONLINE ADOPTION APPLICATION AND A MEMBER OF OUR ADOPTIONS TEAM WILL REACH OUT TO YOU.  Please visit our web site at HSGKC.ORG for an adoption application, our current COVID-19 adoption protocol, and other adoption info. 

> If you decide you'd like to adopt one of the pets you meet, we reserve the pet for you but we generally don't send the pet home with you that day. We’ll instead schedule a pick up date and time that’s convenient for you.   

> Our goal is to send you home with a healthy pet and any information and support you may need to help your new pet adjust to his or her new home.  All of our dogs & puppies have been spayed or neutered, vaccinated, microchipped, dewormed, treated for fleas & ticks, tested for heartworms (7 mo. and over), and are on monthly heartworm preventative. Puppies who are too young to receive all the necessary puppy boosters and/or first rabies shot may be brought back to us for those vaccines at no extra charge. You will also receive a leash, collar, coupons for pet supplies and services, toys, and educational materials. And we'll give your dog a bath before he or she goes home! 

> Please note that we prefer and may require a fenced yard for many of our dogs.  Exceptions are made on an individual basis depending on the dog's needs, the person's dog experience, the dog's and person's activity levels, home environment and other factors. 

Thank you for searching for a shelter pet!

Phone: 913.521.2339

animal.description:
Meet Buddy!

Hello, my name is Buddy. I'm 14 years old, blind, and weigh about 28 pounds. My dad, who took very good care of me my whole life, passed away and there were no family members who could take care of me, so now I'm looking for my brand new forever home. I'm not exactly perfectly housetrained, but that's really an easy fix. If you leave the doog open, I will go potty outside, otherwise I just need tou to take me out on a regular basis. If you are going to be gone, or aren't into waking up in the middle of the night to take me out, I do perfectly fine with a belly band on so I don't have an accident on the floor. I do good with other mellow dogs who like just laying around the house in a nice soft dog bed. I'm not much of a player anymore though, so a more hyper dog who is an in your face type of dog wouldn't be a good fit for me. Much like the dogs I get along with, I also like older, calm, respectful children. I'm not too keen on the idea of having my ears or hair pulled, so little ones who don't understand that are out of the question. 

Foster mom says I'll be a wise friend for my new family. I quickly adjust to new surroundings and learn the ins and outs of my new environment despite not being able to see. My nose works just fine, so I let that do the work of my eyes too! I'm okay laying in a dog bed, and I don't need to always be next to you, but I'm okay with laying on the couch next to you if you help me up. All in all, I'm a pretty low maintenance guy, just looking for a quiet, low key home to make my own! 

Albert's Dog Lounge is a transporting dog rescue, meaning that we rescue many of our dogs from high kill shelters in areas of dog overpopulation. We are a specialty rescue focusing primarily on senior and special needs dogs.  The vast majority of our dogs come from the Houston, TX area where we have an entire team of volunteers, coordinators, and fosters. We do also work with local shelters, rescues, and owners.  If you apply for a dog that is currently in our local Houston program, we will work to get your dog transported to WI as quickly as possible. We ask that you have patience during this time of uncertainty and unprecedented dog adoptions nationwide. 

Learn more about Albert's Dog Lounge, our mission, and adoption policies by visiting Albertsdoglounge.org. 

Our process includes an approved application, reference checks, a homevisit, and then a meet and greet with the dog. Adoption fee is $275.

Begin your application process by copying this link into your web browser: https://www.albertsdoglounge.org/apply

WI Dept. Of Agriculture License Number: 474085-DS

animal.description:
Have you met Miley?

Miley was brought into San Diego Humane Society by her owner who said she no longer had time to care for her properly. Miley is 12 years old, blind, and weighs 17 lbs.

When Miley arrived on January 19th, it was clear that her family hadn't taken the time to get her groomed in a while. After just half a day here, what was even more apparent is that Miley's mentation seemed changed. She walked aimlessly in circles where we constantly had to fish her our from corners, had limited to no awareness of her surroundings, and she was inconsolable- thrashing and crying when held.

The first thing we did was got her cleaned up at the groomer. They had to give her a tight haircut to eliminate the mats. From there, we had the vets evaluate the bloodwork and x-rays that San Diego Humane Society had done, which were overall unremarkable. Miley seemed like she would really benefit from a foster situation, and thankfully, we had volunteers apply to specifically take Miley on a Frosted Fling because they noticed she needed extra love.

For the next couple of weeks we are going to help Miley get comfortable in a home environment and let her decompress. We want to give her every opportunity to thrive while keeping in mind her quality of life.

If you have a knack for providing dignified hospice care, please apply to be Miley's mom or dad: www.frostedfacesfoundation.org/apply/

Visit us at Open House: Saturdays & Sundays, 10 am - 1 pm.

Learn more about our programs at www.frostedfacesfoundation.org/family. No adoption fees, and we help with medical costs!

Become a family: www.frostedfacesfoundation.org/apply

Questions: adopt@frostedfacesfoundation.org

Updated: 1/31/21 KG

animal.description:
Mogwai is a silly, goofy 2 year old catahoula/lab mix who weighs on at 60 pounds. He is currently in a foster home in Seattle, WA and he has come all the way from a shelter in Texas to work with trainers to give him the obedience skills he needs to become the best boy he can be! He is eager to please and is very food motivated, which will help continue his training with you! This will also help him learn any cool tricks you’d like to teach him quickly!

Mogwai would make the perfect hiking partner, or a great buddy for any outdoor activities you might be interested in! He is also happy keeping it low key and chilling in the house or enjoying a movie marathon! He is an independent boy, so he prefers to sit NEXT to his people rather then ON his people.

Mogwai is potty trained, kennel trained, is working on leash training, and enjoys car rides. He is in the process of E-collar training and his E-collar will be included in his adoption fee. 

If we had to characterize Mogwai in a sentence with 15 words or less: A VERY smart, chill, appropriately affectionate, good boy with the softest, most luxurious fur.

*Mogwai’s adoption fee will go towards training with our trainer to ensure he and his new family are off to the best possible start. *

If interested in adopting Mogwai, please fill our our application here: bit.ly/GCSTARSadopt

animal.description:
Let me introduce Poppy! This sweet girl originally came from Texas with her three siblings. All of them were super shy and needed to be socialized. They had been on their own for quite some time. Her three siblings were adopted and she was left alone. Poppy is six months old and weighs about 17 pounds she is Chihuahua and Something unknown.

Poppy is very shy. She is learning to trust and gaining confidence. She needs a home with another dog and someone to be kind and gentle with her. She has a long way to go in building her confidence and learning that life is fun. She is learning to play with toys very slowly. We are working on her leash skills. Because she lacks confidence and is so timid she will need lots of help. Ideally she will go to a home with another smaller dog, must have a fenced in yard and someone who will love to spend time with her. She is completely crate trained and we are working on housebreaking. If you feel that you may be the family that she is seeking please will visit our web page and fill out an application. Poppy is fully vetted including micro chipped. She is current on vaccinations and heartworm prevention. Did I mention she gets along well with cats to? She’s very cat curious but tends to be a little afraid of them.

We require a fenced in yard.  NO EXCEPTIONS.


If interested, please submit an application via our website at www.anassafehavenrescue.org.

Disclaimer: All information we know of Poppy has been provided. If you are able to see this profile, then the puppy is still available. Emails asking if this dog is still available will not be answered. We apologize for this but we receive too many emails when we post our dogs. Please refer to our website for additional information regarding our adoption process.

animal.description:
**WAIT LIST** - This girl has a lot of admirers already, so we're afraid potential adopters will need to stand in line, but she's not adopted yet! So please do apply.


Quizzy, Quizzy, Quizzy!!! 

We love this beautiful poodle mix so much. We can't believe it but she was brought in as a stray, but she made it to Muttville and is ready to be spoiled rotten. She has the cutest little wiggly waggly nubbin tail that wags away when you call her name! She adores pets and gets so excited to get attention and pets. She is a super charmer for sure!

She takes life one step at a time, a little bit slower than others due to vision impairment, but that doesn't stop her from exploring. Quizzy is beyond sweet and so ready to bring more love to your home.

* HERE'S WHAT QUIZZY'S FOSTER MOM HAS TO SAY! *

Quizzy lives up to her name as a very inquisitive little pup! Quizzy has a very calm and gentle demeanor which makes her really well suited for houses with young children or other animals. 
So far she hasn't reacted or responded to other dogs but her absolute favorite activity is snuggling in bed and being close to the humans around her. 

While Quizzy isn't fully blind, her cataracts have impaired her vision. Because of this, she will do best in a single story home though she has done well navigating the 3 steps up to our front door. She was initially resistant to walking on a leash but is really getting the hang of it and enjoys exploring open spaces like parks! Quizzy is house trained and is doing really well with a regular schedule of being taken outside. She isn't super food motivated but really loves positive attention and praise. Quizzy's ready to come sniff and snuggle her way into your heart!

animal.description:
Daisy Lynn
Breed: Beagle mix
Estimated age: 9-11 years old
Weight: 13 pounds

This sweet gal is a former hunting dog who lived outside her whole life. She was given up because she couldn't keep up with the pack anymore. Daisy Lynn can't wait to find a family who will let her relax & live out her golden years.

- Daisy Lynn is still learning to trust & will need a patient adopter who will give her the time & attention she needs
- Loves to be held by her foster mom
- Food makes her very very happy & she is in the process of gaining some weight (she definitely doesn't mind the extra food!)
- Is looking for a home without small who can respect her space 
- Does ok with other dogs but would definitely prefer to be an only child as she likes being left alone
- Being a beagle mix, Daisy Lynn is a vocal girl who loves to sing. No apartments/joint complex living 
- After living outside her whole life & growing used to living in her own squalor Daisy Lynn is not potty trained. She does well with wearing a diaper

Before emailing- please read:
- Yes, this dog is available for adoption
- The adoption fee for Daisy Lynn is $256
- Apply at c2cnd.org
- The adoption fee covers their age appropriate shots, microchip, deworming, spay/neuter, and any other medical expenses while in our care.
- Local adopters only. Due to our thorough adoption process including home visits, we limit our adoptions to local families in the greater Charlotte area.
- If you have any additional questions, email us at dogs@c2cnd.org and we will respond as soon as possible!

Copy and paste the link to access the sign-up genius for an appointment: https://www.signupgenius.com/go/20f084ea8ae2da5f49-meet for dogs and https://www.signupgenius.com/go/20f084ea8ae2da5f49-meet1 for cats.

For animals in FOSTER homes, please submit an online application and an adoption team will reply with next steps. We thank you for your patience as we work to keep saving lives during this difficult time. 

If you are interested in adopting this dog, please fill out our dog adoption questionnaire and e-mail it to elenahtar@gmail.com

PLEASE VISIT THIS WEBSITE TO FIND THE ADOPTION QUESTIONNAIRE:
http://www.homewardtrails.org/adopt-a-pet/adoption-forms/

Buster is quite possibly the cutest 3-year-old mixed Boxer. His white shoes, brindle coat, short legs, and puppy looks will turn heads. On walks, he'll want to say hi to passing dogs and strike out to find the latest scent but is well-trained not to yank you along despite his strength and with reinforcement, will heed you "leave it. He's a ball of love with his human companions and hasn't met anyone, young or old, who he doesn't wanted to say hi to. At home he'll want join you on the couch and either stretch out like the whole 6 feet is his or crawl up in a ball next to you. After a day of exercise, for which he'll both need and thank you for, he'll find either his crate, dog bed, or your bed--if allowed--to curl up and sleep through the night. Buster's favorite activity is wrestling with his friends, including an 8-month-old English Bulldog, but he can be picky about his friends. He enjoys urban hikes and even winter climbing, along with a bit of water fun before it got too cold! Although he's still figuring out why he should run after a toy, once all the new smells are taken in, he's close to enjoying fetch. To be happy in his furever home, he'll do best with a larger yard to explore and release energy but hasn't shown any signs of being the next Houdini. Buster comes housetrained, crate-trained, and great on car rides so he's ready for your own next adventure or just daily life. And he's a fast student having learned lie down in only a day and doing fairly well with all basic commands. He's basically all you could ask for in a dog with a little love and training!

Buster came to us from a rural shelter in WV. He's shown no signs of guarding or aggression towards any humans, regardless of food, toys, or personal space. He has done well with other dogs that match his style of play. 

Adoption Coordinator: Elena
Location: Foster Home

The adoption fee for this dog is $475. This fee INCLUDES spay/neuter and microchip. 

We are proud to partner with the following veterinarians who offer a free first exam for your animal, exclusively for HT adopters: Caring Hands Animal Hospital, Palisades Veterinary Clinic, Sunshine Animal Hospital and Clarendon Animal Care and all VCA Animal Hospitals.

Additionally, any VCA hospital will cover illnesses up to $250 at no cost to any Homeward Trails adopter.

We also provide free online workshop with a professional dog trainer at Fur-Get Me Not within the first 30 days of adopting - just for HT adopters in the Arlington/Alexandria/Falls Church/DC area. Start your new dog out on the right foot with this valuable, expert guidance FREE!

You can save animals like this one by becoming a foster! Fosters are like way stations between high kill shelters and forever homes. We need fosters so that we can save dogs before they are euthanized at the shelters. If you are interested in becoming a foster, please check out our information about fostering by visiting http://www.homewardtrails.org/foster-a-pet/dog-and-cat-foster-program

animal.description:
Murphy was a very scared stray boy at a gas station.  He was secured and placed in a loving foster home where he is learning that people are not all bad.  It is like he doesn't know how to be a dog and is taking cues from the 7-9 small to large breed dogs with whom he is living.  Murphy has come a very long way in his progress but has quite a ways to go yet.  He loves Doritos and thus will now take them from a person's hand.  He will follow people and some times even touch a person with his nose but is scared to have a person touch him.  Although once he is in a person's arms or next to a person, he loves being stroked.  So Murphy is learning and it would be good to find him his forever home who can continue his rehabilitaion and he won't have to move again.  Could you be that loving, patient person or family to help Murphy lern that life with people can be fun?

Murphy is around 4-5 years old, up to date on his vaccines and preventatives, neutered, heart worm negative, house trained and a delightful fellow.

If you are interested in learning more about Murphy, please fill out the Dog Adoption Application on the MARC website www.marc4change.org

Murphy's adoption fee is $200.00.

animal.description: Hello, my name is Torah! I am a big friendly girl that is in need of a new home. I had a home that I loved, but my owner became ill and could not care for me any longer. I was sad to leave, but my owner knew the shelter would do their best to help me find a new home.  So here I am! Ready to try again!  First a little about me! I am a big fluffy terrier mix  that has excellent manners! I already know commands like “sit” and “shake!” I am super dog friendly! In fact I have yet to meet another dog that I didn’t like! I am a wonderful leash walker and great car rider! I am a big girl that weighs about 70 pounds! The shelter made sure I had all of my vaccinations, that I was heartworm negative, that I had a microchip, and that I was spayed. Now here is the thing that worries me the most…..I am about eight years old. Will someone take a chance on me at my age? Oh I sure hope so! You won’t find a more loyal, friendly, and loving companion than me!

Meet Maui!

Maui is a big handsome 6 month old puppy! He is already 56 pounds and will probably top 70 at adulthood. Maui is happy, friendly and gets along well with dogs, kids and adults. Not good with cats. He is looking for a new home due to a divorce and not because of anything he did! This is a sweet boy that will make a great companion dog. He is highly trainable and a great age.  He is super cute with a wrinkled brow, doesn't seem worried though! He is healthy, up to date on shots and neutered. He is ready to travel ASAP!

Maui  is currently in TN but will be transported north to New England for adoption. The adoption donation is $500 which includes a health certificate and costs for his transport north.

*Unless stated otherwise, all dogs will be spayed or neutered, on flea/tick product and heart worm prevention medicine (if older than 5 months) and micro chipped prior to adoption.

*Please note that while we do our best to accurately state the breed or breed mix of a dog, we often have very limited information to draw from. Identifying the breed without pedigrees and information on heritage can be very challenging! 

If you are interested in adopting one of our animals, please go to www.angelsamongusanimalrescue.org and fill out an online adoption application. Thank you!

Massachusett's Residents: Effective September 28, 2017 a Quarantine Fee of $120 will be required  (in addition to the adoption fee) to adopt a dog that has been Quarantined. Massachusetts mandates that all dogs entering MA shall be quarantined for 48 hours in a state approved facility.

animal.description:
Hello everyone! My name is Frankie! I am a chocolate lab mix and I am so sweet! I have lots of energy and I am 10 months old! I would love my forever home to include a fenced yard and another dog to play with! I am easily trainable and I listen once I pick things up. I am smart as a whip and I am super food motivated! I have lots of potential! 

The adoption donation fee is $350 which is tax-deductible and goes towards the care of homeless pets with Pals for Paws. 

To expedite the adoption process you can fill out an application online at www.palsforpawsinc.com/adopt. Please note the adoption application doesn’t bind you to anything. Pals for Paws reserves the right to refuse any adoption application for any reason and at any point in the adoption process. 

To view our other wonderful Homeless Pets visit www.palsforpawsinc.com/pet-list ALSO be sure to LIKE Pals for Paws on Facebook at www.facebook.com/palsforpaws.inc 

All Pals for Paws Rescue animals are fully vetted:
*Spayed/Neutered
*Groomed
*Shots updated plus Leptospirosis 
*Micro-chipped
*Dewormed 
*On Heart-worm prevention
*On Flea and Tick Prevention
* Dentals are done if needed 

You only need to see your vet for a “meet n greet” of your new family member and to turn in their medical records.

Pals for Paws is a 501(c)3 animal rescue. Every penny donated and every penny received through adoption fees goes right back into the organization. There are times when the volunteers have to dip into their pockets to help the animals. We do not euthanize because a pet is sick, heart-worm positive, or has a broken leg; we fix it all, big and small. We strive to go above and beyond when caring for and socializing our animals. We understand the importance of getting to know each and every animal available for adoption in an effort to place them in the most perfect home possible. 
If you are looking for a particular type of dog or have special needs, We can help! Contact us at www.palsforpawsinc.com

animal.description: Our beautiful Maggie is 100 % Central Asian Shepherd Dog,roughly 80lbs, a year old; she is at a very trainable age. Asian Shepherd's are self-assured, balanced, quiet, proud and independent. They are a working dog so she'd love a yard and someone willing to walk/play with her. She is a goofy girl, all legs. Maggie is ok with other dogs but she needs to learn how to play with them. She'll do fine as an only dog or with another large gentle dog. Cats she wants to play with, correctable but may be best without them. Dogs live in the moment. Unfortunately, Maggie will have fewer moments than many, but will you be the person to make those moments awesome for her? She is deserving of a home that can give her all the attention possible.Maggie has a condition called Subaortic Stenosis which makes her life expectancy only 3 to 5 years. She will need to be on a medication called Atenolol, which is fairly cheap, daily for the rest of her life. She has been spayed, micro chipped, vaccinated, and is on HW/Flea preventatives. If you feel you can give Maggie her forever home please email helpsedaliacats@gmail.com or message Cat Assistance Team Sedalia on Facebook.

animal.description:
Hi, my name is Axel!

 

I am almost 5 months old, I'm about 25 lbs right now, and I'm a bulldog, pointer, pit mix. I was surrendered to the rescue as a baby along with my littermates, and it was quickly realized that things were not quite right with me. You see, I have something called a myelomeningocele, also known as spina bifida. I have a large defect in my lower spine, and my spinal cord isn't complete. Surprisingly, my mobility is very normal, but this defect has left me urinary and fecal incontinent. I love my diapers and have been wearing them since I was teeny tiny. I'm a great boy and I always stand still for my diaper changes. At just 12 weeks old, I underwent emergency surgery to reroute my urinary tract due to some major problems I was having going potty. I'm healed from this but I may be prone to urinary tract infection in the future. Sometimes I need help going potty or poop, and my foster mom can teach you how to do this. Because I'm in diapers, I do need butt baths and barrier creams every day, and I am very good for those too. I have a couple of other minor problems that my foster mom can tell you more about if you're interested in adopting me.

 

But, that's enough about my special needs... How about my personality! I am an energetic boy who loves other dogs and people. I would do best in a home with another high energy and tolerant dog. I've grown up with a large breed doggy in my foster home, and he loves me and puts up with my crazy puppy antics. I love cats too, but any cats in my future home need to also be tolerant of me. I tend to chase when I get excited, but I do this out of play and love to tackle and wrestle the cats. I'm slowly learning that this is not ok, but I will need this to be reinforced in my future home if there are cats. While I have my wild moments, my foster mom says I am THE BEST snuggler around and I will sleep in her lap for 10 hours straight if she lets me. The minute the TV goes on, I'm in her lap sprawled out and snoring. She also recently took me on a 20 hour road trip and I slept literally the entire way.

 

I'm looking for a very special family that will love me just the way I am. I'm fully vaccinated, neutered, and am ready for adoption any time!

 

Please apply at www.rejoycefulrescue.com/adopt/adoption-application and my foster mom will reach out to you!

animal.description:
A woman who volunteers for a local shelter saw Shiva alone in a parking lot. Her eyes were sad but her belly was full of life - literally! She was about to pop at any moment! The woman couldn't imagine the thought of this sad girl giving birth on the streets of Houston so she jumped to action. She sweet talked to her and Shiva slowly waddled her way up to her. The woman was able to pick her up and bring her to the shelter right away. Luckily for Shiva, not only was she saved off the streets but her finder had room in her home to take care of her for when she gave birth! Once this sad girl found the dog bed in her foster home, she laid down on it and didn't even move. The dog bed was so comfortable her foster mom had to bring her food and water to her, she wouldn't leave the cozy bed! After awhile, her sad eyes turned into sleepy eyes and she finally felt relaxed enough to fall asleep. Not even a day later she gave birth to 4 beautiful pups in the safety of this temporary home! Shiva is an absolute superstar and is great with cats, dogs AND kids! But despite all of this, her foster is unable to keep her much longer; she needs the space to help other homeless dogs. Although Shiva is thankful to be rescued off the streets, she is looking to be rescued one last time.

We have no back story or update for this dog at this time. When we do, it will be updated here. This is all the information we have currently.

animal.description:
Hi, my name is Wilson! I'm a 3yo, border collie mix & I weigh about 50 lbs, and I love Colorado! I think I was always meant to be a Colorado-dog and just made the long journey from Texas. My life in Texas was kind of rough - I didn't eat very well and as such, I was losing patches of fur! Thankfully though, some nice people got me connected to 2 Blondes All Breed Rescue so I could get a fresh start.

In my foster home, I've learned what love and affection are from tiny humans and big humans. My foster mom says I'm amazing and patient and kind. I only know those things because of what they have shown me! I'm really grateful for my foster home but it's time for me to find my forever home! I'm good with dogs and kids, so I would make an excellent family pet. I would love a yard and/or an active family to take me on adventures with them. I've been working on my leash manners and basic commands but I know I can continue learning these new things in my forever home. 

If I sound like a good pet for your family, please submit an adoption application! I already can't wait to meet you! 

Adoption fee includes the following:


	Spay/Neuter
	Rabies Vaccination
	Distemper / Parvo Vaccines (includes series of 3 for puppies)

If the animal has "HAS APPLICATION" listed, they are still available to receive additional applications but also may be in the process of being adopted soon. Apply for a DOG: http://www.citydogsrescuedc.org/adoptable-dogs.html

Interested in saving more lives? Foster a dog today! Learn more, see our list of dogs needing foster, and apply, https://www.citydogsrescuedc.org/foster-a-city-dog.html

City Dogs Rescue & City Kitties is a foster based rescue in Washington, DC. We do not have a shelter. We focus on local adoptions in DC and the metro area of Maryland and Virginia. CDR&CK has a thorough adoption process in order to find the best possible fit for each of our dogs and cats (we do not operate under a first-come, first served model).

Upon accepting a new cat or dog into the organization, we provide a basic vet visit that includes necessary vaccinations, disease screenings, deworming, microchips, and spay/neuter (unless specified). We do not provide a comprehensive medical exam prior to adoption. As a result, sickness, injury, and disability may exist unbeknownst to CDR&CK. City Dogs Rescue & City Kitties is not responsible for payment of any vet care, including known and unknown medical conditions once a cat or dog is adopted from us. 
Dog specific: Rabies, DHPP, Bordatella vaccines. They are tested for HW, Lyme, Ehrlichia, Anaplasmosis.

Most cats and dogs will have a house training accident in the initial days in their new home and we cannot guarantee any pet is housebroken or crate trained.

We also update our Facebook page daily with new cats and dogs.

This pet is positive for Ehrlichia and Anaplasma, which are common flea/tick-borne illnesses that are treatable and not contagious to other pets as long as they are current on their flea/tick prevention. She requires an active family with breed experience who will provide her with the physical exercise/structure she needs to thrive and the mental stimulation/enrichment she craves to keep her from being bored. She has an intense personality and will require an experienced pet parent. Laika wants to be included in all your adventures (road trips, brewery outings, camping, hanging out with the neighbors.)
Kennel trained: check 
Excellent off-leash recall: check

Albert's Dog Lounge is a transporting dog rescue, meaning that we rescue many of our dogs from high kill shelters in areas of dog overpopulation. We are a specialty rescue focusing primarily on senior and special needs dogs.  The vast majority of our dogs come from the Houston, TX area where we have an entire team of volunteers, coordinators, and fosters. We do also work with local shelters, rescues, and owners.  If you apply for a dog that is currently in our local Houston program, we will work to get your dog transported to WI as quickly as possible. We ask that you have patience during this time of uncertainty and unprecedented dog adoptions nationwide. 

Learn more about Albert's Dog Lounge, our mission, and adoption policies by visiting Albertsdoglounge.org. 

Our process includes an approved application, reference checks, a homevisit, and then a meet and greet with the dog. Adoption fee is $275.

Begin your application process by copying this link into your web browser: https://www.albertsdoglounge.org/apply

Rosco is a great Lab mix weighing 40 lbs at 1 .5 years in age.  He was picked up as a stray in AR.  He is an active guy with med/high energy who just loves to run and play.  He will do best in a home with another dog to exert his energy, and pet parents who will spend time teaching him how to be the best boy ever!  Rosco has been good with other dogs, but has not been cat tested.  He gets so excited when he meets people that he jumps for joy and could be a bit overwhelming to smaller children.  He can also climb a chain link fence to be with his people, so needs a stockade or high picket fence instead.  This pup is a sweetheart and will thrive in a home where he receives the attention he so deserves!

Please Note: Rosco is currently being fostered in AR and is not here to meet.  It is very likely he will receive a deposit for his adoption before arriving in MA.  Please read more about our rescue and process on our website www.foreverhomerescue.org.  If interested, the first step in our process is to complete an application.  We find our pup's do best in a home with children ages 5 and older.

Please complete an online APPLICATION if you wish to adopt.  Forever Home Rescue New England is a 501(c)3  non-profit organization. We are a network of foster homes in the South and the New England area. THERE IS NO SPECIFIC SHELTER LOCATION. If you wish to meet our dogs, you must first be approved by going through our application and screening process. Forever Home Rescue suggests obedience training for all puppies and dogs. All dogs are up to date on their shots, dewormed and spayed or neutered. Vet fees, transport fee and New England quarantine fees ARE INCLUDED in each dog's adoption fee. Also, any dogs older than pups--even if they are not marked housetrained in their posting---usually housetrain within a day or two, because most are used to living outside in the south and will prefer to do their business outdoors. Our dogs and pups are best suited for families with children 5 yrs old and up. If you are approved to adopt, please submit the $100 deposit by clicking on our rescue's name in this posting (Forever Home Rescue New England--in purple) which will bring you to a new page with the deposit link at the bottom.  STOP! If you have not been notified of your approval status do not make a deposit.

animal.description:
Wrangel is a fun, happy 18 month old lab greyhound mix looking for an active home where he will be included in your life and all of your adventures.
A sweet, energetic boy who enjoys lounging around after getting in daily exercise. 
He will bring happiness to your life with his infectious smile and his joy for life. 
Loves to play with humans, other dogs, getting treats, affection and being with his people. 
Will be a great running, hiking, biking and adventure companion with his long leggy, muscular body.
He's a fast boy, whether running around the yard, playing or on the trails. 
An adopter willing to attend training classes with him, give him a routine and daily exercise will be rewarded with a loving, loyal 'full of life' guy. 
Housetrained and crate trained.
Sleeps through the night in his crate.
Walks nicely on leash for a short distance, but will need some more consistent training to 'wrangle' in his excitement to keep moving and exploring.
Rides well in the car - gets a little excited at first knowing that he's going somewhere with his people, but settles down.
Not an incessant barker, but will bark a little when he's overly excited.
Dog friendly with most well - socialized small and large dogs. As with all dogs, proper introductions are necessary.
Wrangel really likes human company and prefers not to be left alone. He thrives with human attention. 
Not destructive inside or outside, but if left unsupervised, he will help himself to the trash can, so those need to be secured. 
Knows some basic commands and would love to learn more.
Very treat motivated and easily redirects with a quick verbal command.
Due to his exuberant energy, we are recommending a home with children over 15.
Cats are unknown, so we will not be adopting him to a home with cats.   
Only homes with a fully fenced yard where he will not be left home alone for long hours will be considered.
Wrangell is 70 lbs, neutered, microchipped, up to date on vaccines including rabies, has been treated for heartworms and is current on prevention.

The adoption fee is $300 which covers initial vetting and other needs plus a transport fee of $175, total adoption cost is $475.

If you are interested in adopting Wrangle, please complete an adoption application on https://www.westernaustralianshepherdrescue.com/.

animal.description:
WOOKIE is 16 years old and weighs 16 pounds.

Woo - Woo - Wookie, that's me. Though I don't think you'll find me as tall as those hirsute bipeds on Star Wars, I do however have hair all over my body like them. I think I am more interesting too.

I am a great family dog and like to protect (my food too), despite being the very definition of a senior dog at 16 years old. I'm doing pretty good, although I think I am going a bit deaf because I don't hear commands very well now. Maybe no one is trying to boss me around though anymore - hahaha. Right now I live with a small poodle who is even older than me (17 years old!) and a three year old golden doodle. How's that for a pack?

I love my walks, but barely get out anymore because of the pandemic –  my human doesn't want to go much. I only go in the yard now. I would really love to see more real estate besides that yard. That's probably why I pee in the house a lot because I'm not getting walks. My human thinks I'm getting old and incontinent and puts me in a belly band. If you don't know what that is it's a doggy diaper that is designed for boys and fits around their private parts. It's rather embarrassing to talk about this with strangers - but there you have it. So you'll have to be patient with me and work on the potty-training or the "diaper" changing part. I will do my best - promise!

I cannot wait to find my forever home, but am sad to be leaving this one where I have been all my life. Call soon please!


 
INTERESTED in WOOKIE? The first step is to fill out our online Adoption Application (address link below)

NOTE: All of our dogs live in foster homes so it is not possible to setup a meet and greet prior to submitting an adoption application. Filling out an application doesn't obligate you to adopt, but it does save your place in line if there are multiple people interested.
 
ADOPTION APPLICATION (Type or cut & paste the below website address into your browser): http://www.sdroregon.com/adoption-application.htm
 
If our Adoption Coordinator determines you are a good match they will contact you. This is a great opportunity for you to find out more about WOOKIE and decide if you would like to setup a meet and greet.  
 
ADOPTION FEE is $150, and there’s a 10% Discount for Senior Citizens and Veterans.
 
Learn more about the ADOPTION PROCESS here (Type or cut & paste the below website address into your browser): http://www.sdroregon.com/adoption-process.htm
 
We apologize, but we are not able to answer individual questions about our dogs. We are a small, all-volunteer organization and we receive hundreds of inquiries. If you want to learn more about a particular dog, then please submit an Adoption Application. If your application is chosen, you will have the opportunity to meet the dog and to get answers to all of your questions. Thank you for your understanding.

Despite being very timid and fearful at first, Caboodle is so affectionate once he is comfortable. He is a MAJOR cuddle monster and loves attention. He will give you puppy eyes and throw himself on his back and stick his legs in the air to show you that he needs his belly rubbed!! He will also put his paw on your arm and stare at you until you pet him. He loves going for walks and could run forever if I could keep up with him. He gets the zoomies if you ask if he wants to go outside and also loves sticking his head out the window during car rides. Although he doesn't seem to have a real interest in toys, he likes to play chase and likes people-watching out the window. 

In addition, his huge ears make him a GREAT listener and is very easy and cooperative on the leash. He is potty/house trained (except he has occasional accidents when he is really scared). He won't eat things off the table or chew on household items. He is also very good at telling you if he needs something and will whine if he needs to go outside or is hungry. Caboodle is quite curious about his surroundings and other people, just a bit scared. 

Caboodle is basically a chill dog who will cuddle all day but loves to be very active as well. He needs a calm environment without children. He needs a patient home for him to build trust and become comfortable. Overall, Caboodle is so sweet, so funny, and so loving.

I'm in a foster home! Please email: foster@kcpetproject.org to meet me!
