animal.description:
Fallon is one of 3 dogs surrendered due to apt. restrictions.  They were all so scared and the Chicago Team worked with them to get them out safe.  We have her dad ROMEO too.  

We felt these 2 needed us most. Fallon shook with fear in her kennel we were not sure we would earn her trust.  
Well the magic of having other dogs in your foster home is all it took.  She is warming up to those she knows and follows cues from others.  Fallon bonded quickly to her foster mom and will do the same wherever she lands.  She will pick her person to help her transition.  

Fallon is part deer, she leaps over effortlessly, only to go visit the neighbors dogs.  Then she returns on the front porch.  So she would need a safe home with containment and supervision.  

A very smart girl, not to mention her beauty.  Fallon is ready and waiting for her new beginning and are so proud of all progress she has made.

www.fourleggedranch.com for an application

animal.description:
Foster To Adopt.

Miller is a 2-year-old super sweet reported to be a hound mix (But we feel that he's a Doberman) that has been diagnosed with heartworm disease. He requires a foster-to-adopt and must be kept on a strict exercise restriction until further notice. The foster-to-adopt must be able to medicate Miller twice a day for at least a month. It is also imperative that they can bring him to the shelter on very specific dates for treatment. Illness can't stop this gorgeous dog from living a full life. Is he the right one for you!

We ensure all of the animals adopted through our shelter are vaccinated, microchipped, and spayed or neutered.

If you love animals but cannot adopt, sponsoring an animal in our care is a meaningful way to help support the good work we do. For as little as $20 per month, you can sponsor a shelter pet and help pay for the cost of their care while they stay at the shelter. Secure your sponsorship online at njshelter.org.

animal.description:
If you are interested in adopting this dog, please fill out our dog adoption questionnaire and e-mail it to elenahtar@gmail.com.

Effective March 18, 2020 all animals available for adoption through Homeward Trails can be met by appointment only. Our Adoption Center public hours are suspended until further notice. Cats dwelling at Crumbs & Whiskers can be met by approved adopters only by appointment. Please submit an online application and an adoption coordinator will reply with next steps. We thank you for your patience and we hope to keep saving lives during this difficult time. 

PLEASE VISIT THIS WEBSITE TO FIND THE ADOPTION QUESTIONNAIRE: http://www.homewardtrails.org/adopt-a-pet/adoption-forms/

Bobby-Lee is a lovely, laid back 2 y.o. hound from Rockbridge, VA and was rescued from a felony cruelty case. Most recently he lived with a family with two kids and another dog for the last 9 months. He is currently with a foster family. He is good with other dogs and loves people. He warms up quickly and likes to snuggle. He has done well on his walks and with people and other dogs. He does have a strong prey drive but does pretty well on a leash. He is mostly house trained just need frequent trips outside. Bobby would love a house with a fenced yard as he loves the outdoors most of all and likes the exercise. He is not very fond of crates and he has some separation axiety so would do best with people who are home a lot and/or willing to work on this with him.

Adoption Coordinator: Elena Kleifges
Location: Foster Home
The adoption fee for this dog is $475. This fee INCLUDES spay/neuter and microchip. 

We are proud to partner with the following veterinarians who offer a free first exam for your animal, exclusively for HT adopters: Caring Hands Animal Hospital, Palisades Veterinary Clinic, Sunshine Animal Hospital and Clarendon Animal Care and all VCA Animal Hospitals.

Additionally, any VCA hospital will cover illnesses up to $250 at no cost to any Homeward Trails adopter.

We also provide a 45 minute online workshop with a professional dog trainer at Fur-Get Me Not within the first 30 days of adopting - just for HT adopters in the Arlington/Alexandria/DC area. 

You can save animals like this one by becoming a foster! Fosters are like way stations between high kill shelters and forever homes. We need fosters so that we can save dogs before they are euthanized at the shelters. If you are interested in becoming a foster, please check out our information about fostering by visiting http://www.homewardtrails.org/foster-a-pet/dog-and-cat-foster-program/

animal.description:
Gail is about 4 or 5 yrs of age. She came to us through our rescue partners in Mississippi. She has been treated for heartworms and parasites and we recently did a dental and mass removal. Turns out the masses were benign so nothing bad there. She is on some medications for her heart but other than that is in good shape. She loves to cuddle and lay with other dogs. She does REQUIRE another dog and a yard and she also REQUIRES a dog door, if you do not have them, please do not apply for her. She likes car rides and dog parks. She has some puppy behavior and will chew some items. We just found out her cough is from heart damage from the heart worms. we have scheduled an echocardiogram to determine the extent of damage

adoption fee is $375 Adoption fees go back to and cover all of the medical for all of the dogs. All dogs are spayed/neutered, vaccinated and micro chipped upon adoption and many have received further treatment for such things as lump removal, severe ear infections, leg injuries, etc..
For more information or to submit an adoption application, please visit our website at http://www.southernnevadabeaglerescue.com . We are also on Facebook at https://www.facebook.com/SouthernNevadaBeagleRescueFoundation . Come meet and play with our available dogs at Las Vegas area dog parks. Times and locations can be found at http://www.meetup.com/beagles-207/ . Contact us or check our Facebook updates ahead of time if you are interested in meeting a particular dog. All our dogs are in foster homes so not all are available to attend all our park meetups.
Our meetup group playdates allow you to socialize your beagle with his/her own breed at dog parks with large fenced areas where the beagles can run and play off-leash. Beagle enthusiasts, come bay with us..... AROOOOOOOOOOOO!

animal.description:
Female, Senior (age unknown), Mixed breed (possibly Miniature Pinscher and Border Collie) weighing ~27 lbs.

-She is up to date with vaccines including rabies, and copies of proof can be provided. She was also spayed.

-Her prior medical conditions have been resolved.

-She wears cute dresses to help hide her hair loss.

-A little more about her personality and behavior, she's fearful of sudden movements and loud noises but relaxes with soft stroking on her head. She's either mostly calm and can sleep all day OR she gets very curious and likes to follow you around like a shadow. She doesn't enjoy play-time with toys, however. (We think because she doesn't know how to play with toys- instead gets scared of them).

-She has bonded with current owners' puppy so we know she does well with other dogs, but it's not known how she does with kids. It's unlikely with very young or active kids for reasons listed above.

-Marina is highly intelligent and is still surprisingly trainable for her age. She responds to her newly given name and learned commands like "sit" (with treats in hand) as well as "stay" before exiting the door on a leash. She also gives you her paws to wipe on the rug.

-She loves long walks and stopping every 2 feet to pick up scents.

-She's proven to be quite the roadrunner and can keep up with other pups at the park!

-She also loves car rides and waits to be safely strapped in.

-She goes H.A.M. for ham and enjoys peanut butter and dog treats like "Pupperoni". She ignores fruits, lol.

-Having kibble with a little bit of olive oil makes her go potty easier.

-Speaking of food, she's so formal! Marina practices proper dinner etiquette by waiting to eat until owners sit down with their meal.

-She absolutely hates getting her teeth brushed, and accepts showers and hair trims because pretty-looking divas have no other choice.

-She doesn't like to be left completely alone. Either the presence of the owner or another dog seems to give her sense of security.

Marina needs experienced and patient dog owners with a calm environment. Owners are trying very hard to avoid surrender at shelter. Thank you!

If interested, please contact Veronica at 305-310-3779

-Good with OLDER (10+) children
-Needs WORK WITH DOGS

Jax is a very shy boy, who is looking for someone to love him. He is learning how to trust people again after being sent to the shelter. At first he will be very timid and feel lost. Once I got him out of the shelter he was a different dog. He was shy at first but is very loving. He loves to cuddle and will make a great pet at his forever home."

animal.description: Cute as can be Harley is about 4 yrs old and weighs approx 42lbs.  He is a silly bulldog that loves to hang out and play with his adult friends.  He has been abused by men in the past so although sometimes he is very affectionate with some men, he does have trust issues so an easy going, gentle and affectionate , yet assertive home is required   He’s not fond of young children so an adult only home is also required.  He also does not like other animals so he must be the only animal in the home.  He does fine on a leash when he sees other animals, as long as they keep their distance.  Instead of long walks, Harley would prefer to go for a short walk and then run around the yard and play with his people.  He must have a securely fenced yard.  AN EXPERIENCED HOME WITH STRONG TEMPERED, DOMINANT  BREEDS IS REQUIRED.  If you are interest in meeting Harley please email info@k9rr.org and include your phone number.

animal.description: Meet Royal! This Terrier Mix is an ADORABLE 4-5 month old pup who weighs about 17 pounds. His foster family says he's been doing excellent with potty training and doing his business outside. He is still like a little skiddish on a leash but has been opening up and making great progress. He's learning commands like come and sit, and has been working on his puppy mouthiness with a "no bite" command. Royal sleeps a lot and LOVES to snuggle. He is mostly interested in chewing on a buly stick or nylabones, he loves rubber toys and prefers them to squeaky and plush toys. He likes meeting other dogs but is slow and timid, but is always receptive to their attention and looks for humans at approval. His foster family hasn't heard him bark much and has mostly seen him be timid and gente. Royal has been going to the park and making friends with small and medium pups, but the big guys intimidate him a bit. He is getting more confident and blossoming in his foster home every day. Royal is up to date on vaccines and neutered.

animal.description:
January Update: Caldwell is still nervous but has started to adjust to his new environment. He relaxes a lot around his friend Clive, and we can see glimpses of his gentle personality. He knows at least the sit command and is very gentle when taking treats from volunteers.
Caldwell was one of 3 dogs picked up in the same area. All three are petrified of shelter life. Lovely trembles in fear; Clive we could not even get out of the kennel he was so scared. Caldwell was less scared than the other two, but you can see the fear in his eyes. He stayed in a hunched position until he noticed Lovely in the kennel across the yard. He cautiously made his way to her and stood there, almost a protective nature. We put him in the kennel next to Lovely to see if that helped her relax, but she did not. He feels the need to protect Lovely and reacted when Opal growled at her. We would love a foster home for Caldwell and Lovely so we can see their true personalities out of the shelter environment.

Caldwell is currently a resident at Vermilion Parish Animal Control. He will be vaccinated, neutered, and microchipped upon placement in an adoptive or foster home. To adopt, complete the adoption application at AAVArescue.com.

animal.description:
Isabelle was literally on her way to the euth room when we called the shelter and said WAIT.  We are coming for her.  She was so shut down and scared.  Now...she has come out of her shell and is a love bug. She loves to say hi to to anyone who wants to say hello, but she is not aggressive about it.  She would probably do well with medium sized dogs with medium energy.  Smaller dogs seem to be intimated by her.  She loves to go on long walks and play fetch with a tennis ball!

----From her Foster---

Isabelle l is a beautiful brown friendly PITBULL, about 3 years old and weighs 60lbs of pure muscle.  She has white “ballet slippers” marking on all four paws, and has the cutest waddle when she walks.  She is very good on a leash, but also follows her nose and can pull quite handily sometimes.  She is very interested in squirrels and possibly chasing squirrels, and she actually caught one once, and dropped the squirrel when I commanded her to do so.  The squirrel ran away somewhat embarrassed, and Isabel had a big smile.  She is single and loves to mingle:  She loves to meet other dogs and other humans, but she can look intimidating to those not familiar with pit bulls, and hence not all dogs want to meet her.  She is very social and hardly ever barks.  She does snore, but it is very cute and well worth sleeping next to her.  She has a lot of love to give.  When I first received her after being transported from the shelter she was very afraid and would not come out of her crate.  However, sleeping next to her crate, in the middle of the night she came out, enjoyed getting pets, and went on a short walk and she instantly showed her love and appreciation for being in a foster home.  And we’ve had a terrific foster relationship ever since.  I’m not able to keep her, as we have 3 rescue cats and my wife thinks that Isabel is just too strong for her to handle when I’m away.  But she is a fantastic dog and could be the perfect companion!

home_environment_attributes.other_animals: She would do well with other dogs with medium energy.

Information: Scrappy came to us as a neglect and abuse case. He likes to play with other dogs, is not reactive to cats, and needs understanding children. He will tense up still with any human touch but is working on it. He loves treats, zoomies with friends, and snuggling under the covers. He enjoys the outdoors. 

 

We are a foster based rescue based out of Muskegon, MI. We have an application process for adopting our pets. We have an application on our website www.caninesrescue.com. LOOKING FOR THE ADOPTION APPLICATION FORM? 
Please visit our website at: www.LHAR.dog 

If application is approved, pup will be held for you to meet/adopt 

(Appointment will be scheduled after application is approved) 

Location: WagsMore Adopt & Shop
                  450 Prospect Blvd, Frederick MD 21701
 
Age of pup: approx 7 months old as of January 2021 
   
The adoption donation for these pups: is $375.00 

This includes: Age appropriate vaccines and dewormings, rabies vaccine, hw prevention and spay

Size:  Medium when full grown 
Breed: Pittie/Hound is best guess?

Petfinder's Dog Size Recommendations:

Small: 25 lbs and under (11 kg)
Medium: 26–60 lbs (12 – 27 kg)
Large: 61–100 lbs (28 – 45 kg)
Extra Large: 101 lbs or more (46 kg)

Please note our requirements to adopt a young puppy. 

1. Fill out our online application at: Www.LHAR.dog 

2. We require all current pets in the household to be up to date on shots and be spayed/neutered. Veterinary references will be contacted. 

3. We require that someone be in the home/work from home half of the work day throughout the work week. It is not healthy for a puppy to be crated and left alone for 5 or more hours a day. Lunch breaks are not considered home half the work day and asking a neighbor to stop in is not considered home half the day. 

Her Story: 

LHAR rescued this sweet girl with the help of an organization in rural WV. Pearl appears to have been born deaf. She does very well with scent and is learning some sign language. As a young pup she appears to have sustained an impact injury to her front left leg. Despite several surgical attempts to save the leg, it was not possible, and amputation was the best option for Pearl's recovery. She is a happy and affectionate girl. She loves other dogs and doesnt seem to mind cats. She will do best in a home with other dogs and a fenced in yard. Experience with deaf dogs is prefered. 

Medium  when full grown. 
  
She is being fostered in a private home 

Weight: approx  40 lbs bs as of January 21st        
 
Photos were taken on January 21st         

Questions? Please email: lharinfo@gmail.com

Adoption donation fees: Please know that 100% of our fees go towards the rescue of puppies and dogs in need. Lonely Hearts Animal Rescue is a 501c3 non profit organization.

Thank you for considering a rescue pup!

animal.description:
These are the best and quiet dogs. They love toys and share well with each other. They are very good at sleeping through the night or when not being interacted with. They will whine for a tiny bit if they think they have been "ignored" long enough. They travel well in the car and usually just lay down and then start popping up looking out the window if it takes too long. Cooper is the biggest and a male. He is a little timid in new situations but once he gets to know you he is all up in your space. He sometimes will take treats away from a sibling if they are willing. He is very calm and chill. He likes to snooze when not playing or eating. Cleo is the smallest and a female. She is feisty but small. The bigger sister will sometimes try to keep her from the food bowl but she just waits and goes in and eats. She will wrestle with the best of them. She is super sweet. She has grown so confident with me. At first, she was not trusting of humans but now she wants to give kisses. Chloe is the middle sister. She has the "Jan" syndrome. If someone else is getting attention she is all up in it. She will leave everyone alone when they have treats. She will start to chew one but loves human affection better. She will flip on her back for a belly rub every time she sees you. She likes to wrestle with anyone but especially her younger sister. Sometimes she takes it too far so I just say be nice or no if she doesn't stop the first time. She is probably the alpha of the group. Please let me know if you need anything else. They are doing great!

Update: Chloe is still a lover of attention and great at giving kisses. She will take and enjoy her treat just like her siblings. She has gotten so big and now has a black stripe on her tail. She enjoys playing with toys. She will still wrestle with the best of them. She has started to run from getting her medicine but will take it.

We have no back story or update for this dog at this time. When we do, it will be updated here. This is all the information we have currently.


	Approved Applicants may make the adoption fee payment by clicking donate above. Partial adoption fees will not hold a dog.
	Dogs adopted with our rescue come with FREE training from #GoodPup to help you build strong bonds from the start!
	If upon meeting the dog of your choosing at an adoption event you find that you aren't a good match, your deposit will be refunded minus a 10% administration fee.
	Adoption fees include vaccines up until time of adoption, microchip, spay/neuter and 1st 30 days of free Pet insurance. We are not affiliated with Pet First pet insurance. (you have to sign up for the insurance or it will not go into effect). 
	Adopters can go to our vet for medical issues that may arise in 1st 3 days of adoption. 
	The dogs in our care are fostered in Colorado, Texas, and New Mexico. While all dogs are picked up during our scheduled times, sometimes transport dates change due to unforeseen circumstances.

animal.description:
Two year old Axel sure is eye candy. This boy's nub never stops! Axel has a lovely temperament and was a shelter favorite. His dog test was on leash and while eager to meet the other dog, he showed no aggression and responded to his handler's direction to sit.. Axel LOVES to play fetch and independently brings the ball back to place at your feet, 

As far as adding him to a home that already has a dog, Axel is very strong and in your face with other dogs, not in a dominant way, but in a sheer excited way. He is so exuberant that he can overwhelm them with his boisterous, rough, in-your-personal-space-clueless excitement. We have been thinking about changing his post to ‘only dog’ not due to aggression, but due to his unsocialized play style. We could see another dog escalating and Axel not realizing he was the cause of it. If you already have a dog, Axel will need one who recognizes his intent and enjoys hard core play. 

**If you are serious about adopting , you must head to our website at www.kodisclub.org and submit a completed application . We will not do anything without an app. Due to the small size of our volunteer-run rescue, only the approved adopter may be contacted. It is not first come first served, but the best match. Yes, if you are reading this, the dog is available so no need to check **

Fudge is probably around 18 weeks old (1/21/2021) & has been fully vaccinated. She will soon be spayed & microchipped. She is full of energy & would love an active family!

For more information about Fudge, contact Susan at daiseymaggie@yahoo.com

animal.description:
IF YOU ARE INTERESTED IN ADOPTING DAMON, PLEASE GO TO OUR WEBSITE TO READ ABOUT THE PROCESS AND FILL OUT AN APPLICATION. www.furkidrescue.org 


Damien was rescued with his dog friend, Kiera, in mid-December. They are local dogs, and their owner passed away a year ago. The landlord had been caring for them, and finally reached out for help. That’s how they got to us. 

Damien is a senior dog and is 110+ pounds of pure love, just looking for someone to spoil him in his old age. After being examined by our vet, we are now treating him for disc disease, which is being managed with steroids. He sometimes needs help getting up off the ground, and will need to be kept on the first floor of a home with stairs. We are looking for a home that he will not have to do any stairs, inside or outside. The steroids have helped him tremendously- he will trot around by himself no problem. He loves toys, particularly ones that give him a little mental stimulation, and he will stay outside and lay in the grass all day if you let him, so a fenced in outdoor area is a bonus! He is house trained, but because of his injury he has some problems with incontinence that can be easily managed with a diaper or by keeping him in an area that can be easily sanitized. He is good with cats and other dogs, and loves getting attention and belly rubs from anyone who comes by!

animal.description:
Meet Atlas! This fluffy, long-legged boy is estimated to be between about 1 1/2 years old. We are calling him a Great Pyr/Collie mix. He currently weighs 53 lbs, but needs to put on some more weight.

Atlas recently arrived in Maine and was a little timid at first, but is now beginning to settle into his foster home. He is doing well with the resident dog and has been great with the two cats so far. He likes to ride in cars.

Atlas is a very gentle, sweet-natured guy. Everyone at the vet's office loved him when he came in for his exam. We think he will make a nice family dog.

History: Atlas was discovered wandering the back roads of Simpson County, Mississippi. He was not wearing a collar or microchip, and nobody claimed him on the area's lost and found website.

Atlas has been neutered and is up-to-date on vaccinations. He is being fostered in southern Maine.

Adoption fees cover age specific vaccinations, spay/neuter, microchip, heartworm/lyme/ehrlichia test, worming and transport fees. 

Adoption fees: 
Through 6 months of age $450; 
7 months to through 5 years $400; 
6 years and under 9 years $325: bonded pairs are $500; 
9 years and older $250: bonded pairs are $300 

Almost Home Rescue of New England is a 501 c 3 non-profit rescue; rescuing dogs since 2005. All Adoption applications are completed on line at www.almosthomerescue.net 

This dog is available unless it is marked as Pending, meaning Pending Adoption. This dog is in foster care locally, ONLY if Maine or New Hampshire is listed next to the dogs name; otherwise, the dog is still waiting with our partner rescue for an adoption or foster home in New England. 

PLEASE NOTE - We will check your veterinary reference, to ensure that current and prior dogs have a history of being kept up to date on rabies and distemper, have had annual heartworm tests, and are on heartworm preventative at least 6 months of the year. Current pets must by spayed/neutered. 

Imported dogs are transported on a USDA approved transport with a Health Certificate. All imported dogs are quarantined 14 days prior to getting on transport.

animal.description:
Meet Raven. Raven has been with us since October 1st.  As far as we can tell, her initial rescuer and her foster… that’s the only peopling she’s ever done. 

When Raven came to us she was approximately 4/5 months old and completely terrified and would tremble and cower back from any touch or interaction. Raven has come such a long way, she now asks for affection(but only in the morning and only if you don’t act too excited for it), she chooses to be in the same room we are in, she will play with the other dogs inside instead of only outside away from the humans, she eats her food even when we are standing next to her and will take a treat from our hands! This beautiful girl will be a very easy companion for someone, small kids probably not a great idea simply because she doesn’t care for loud or sudden noises. 
Raven has not one ounce of nervous aggression she simply needs time to trust that you’re a good human! 
Raven will take time, love and patience but the reward of her love and trust makes it easy! 

Raven is an 8 month old lab mix. She is current on shots, heart worm and flea and tick prevention, spayed, and microchipped.

animal.description:
Betsy is a 7-year-old mixed breed rescued from a high-kill shelter. This dog is current on vaccinations, microchipped, 4dx/heartworm tested, and spayed/neutered. This dog is also tested with other dogs, kennel-trained, and housebroken. We would love for you to meet this dog and see if it might be a good fit for your home. 

The first step to adoption is completing an adoption application on our website at www.bounceanimalrescue.org. Pending approval, your application is valid for 1 year, and you will be eligible to request a hold on an individual animal. The hold does not require that you adopt the animal, but ensures you get to meet and make an adoption decision prior to other applicants. Hold times cannot exceed 5 days. Also pending approval, you will be able to acquire foster home contact information, so you inquire on personalities of specific animals.

***COVID-19 Update: While we typically host weekly Saturday adoption events, in order to follow the CDC's recommendation for COVID-19 protocols, we will be suspending our weekly Saturday adoption events until given the clear. Adoptions for individual animals will occur by private adoption appointment and/or adoption handoff. Appointments and handoffs are scheduled pending staff, foster home, and vetting schedules. Because we are 100% foster-based, adoption appointments and handoffs are only offered for individual animals. When adopting at an appointment, please be aware that you will be taking the animal home that day. We can not hold animals to be picked up at a later date.

Due to CDC's recommended COVID-19 protocols, we are highly encouraging foster homes and adopters to speak with one another via phone or video chat to ensure compatible matches and limit in-person contact. If meeting in person, our foster homes are encouraged to wear masks, socially distance, and choose an outdoor meeting spot. Should you want to proceed forward with the adoption, all adoption paperwork, medical records, and adoption fees are to be completed electronically. Quick and low-contact animal handoff is also being encouraged amongst foster homes and adopters. As always, we include a one-week trial period with all our adoptions. ***

Please note, we do not have the ability to process adoption applications at our adoption events, so please plan accordingly. If an application is submitted past 5pm on Monday-Thursday, it will begin review the following day. If submitted on Friday-Sunday, it will begin review on Monday. It takes approximately 48-72 hours for an application to be processed.

For additional questions regarding meeting this dog please contact us via text/email at 970.699.6772, or contact@bounceanimalrescue.org. We apologize for any inconvenience, but due to a high volume of inquiries, calls and voicemails regarding adoption will not be returned.

Thank you for choosing adoption! If you would like more information on our organization please visit our website at www.bounceanimalrescue.org.

animal.description: Luna is a sweet young girl who is making fast friends with just about everyone at PACC. We're told that in her previous home, she lived with kids from newborns to age 12 and was fantastic. While she loves people, she's a little more selective when it comes to other dogs (and isn't a fan of small ones) so for that reason, we're going to require a meet-and-greet for any resident dogs. Luna's former owners had this to say about her: Luna is an amazing dog. She is sweet and loving. She is loyal to her person. Her favorite toys are huge stuffed animals. We call them her babies and she totes them all over the house. It's so cute. In play group, Luna was nervous at first, then became social and friendly, initiating and engaging in in a little bit of play. Luna also enjoyed the pool and was friendly to her handlers. If Luna sounds like the girl for you, make an appointment to meet her today.

animal.description:
Meet Scruffy! Scruffy weighs 32 lbs and is just over a year old. Our best guess is that Scruffy is a Lab/Terrier mix.

Scruffy gets along with adult dogs but does not have a lot of patience with puppies. His best buddies at the shelter were two large male mixed breed dogs. Scruffy has not been cat-tested.

Scruffy has a silly personality and will do the cutest little head tilt when you talk to him, as if he's trying hard to understand what you're saying. He wants to bond with his person so badly, and will be a most loyal companion.

Scruffy gets nervous in new situations and will need some time to decompress and get his bearings. We therefore feel he would not be good match for households with small children. His perfect home would be a bit more rural, with another larger, older dog to help show him the ropes. Someone who has experience with rescue dogs would be ideal.

Scruffy has been neutered and is up-to-date on his vaccinations. He is being fostered in southern Maine.

Adoption fees cover age specific vaccinations, spay/neuter, microchip, heartworm/lyme/ehrlichia test, worming and transport fees. 

Adoption fees: 
Through 6 months of age $450; 
7 months to through 5 years $400; 
6 years and under 9 years $325: bonded pairs are $500; 
9 years and older $250: bonded pairs are $300 

Almost Home Rescue of New England is a 501 c 3 non-profit rescue; rescuing dogs since 2005. All Adoption applications are completed on line at www.almosthomerescue.net 

This dog is available unless it is marked as Pending, meaning Pending Adoption. This dog is in foster care locally, ONLY if Maine or New Hampshire is listed next to the dogs name; otherwise, the dog is still waiting with our partner rescue for an adoption or foster home in New England. 

PLEASE NOTE - We will check your veterinary reference, to ensure that current and prior dogs have a history of being kept up to date on rabies and distemper, have had annual heartworm tests, and are on heartworm preventative at least 6 months of the year. Current pets must by spayed/neutered. 

Imported dogs are transported on a USDA approved transport with a Health Certificate. All imported dogs are quarantined 14 days prior to getting on transport.

animal.description:
Apply at: http://www.plannedpethood.org/adopt/available-dogs.html

Hi, I'm Duke. I'm a 6 year old coonhound mix. I am a very sturdy 90 pounds but my people think that I need a diet, whatever that is. I just know that I love food and don't like to share it with the other dogs. I had to be surrendered when my previous owner got very sick and could not take care of me even though I was very loved. I am a super laid back guy. I love to just lounge around and hang out with my people. I am great with kids and cats. I am pretty good with other dogs so long as they are laid back like me. My fosters have a 4 year old lab that I am great with but I think that the 7 month old boxer puppy is a little annoying. He likes to jump on me and try to get me to play but I would rather snooze. I am a very well mannered boy. I do not need to be crated and am fully housebroken. I am very devoted to my people and love to be wherever they are. I am okay on a leash and don't pull but when I pick up a scent, I want to follow it so I sometimes get a little distracted. All in all, I am a very sweet boy just looking for a loving family to call my own. If you are interested in meeting Duke, please fill out an application. 

Please understand the statements about this animal are based upon the foster home's evaluation of the animal.  The animal might behave differently (negatively or positively) in your home.  While the animal might be good with the current foster’s dogs, cats, children, etc., it may not be with your animal(s) or children.  The animal may be housebroken or litter trained in the home of the foster but may relapse in your home.  The animal is represented to the public as it performs in the foster home and any statements made regarding the animal are conditional to that foster home setting.  Those interested in adopting should have read all information about the animal and understand they cannot claim they did not understand the facts about this animal as understood by Planned Pethood and/or the foster.  Planned Pethood and vet(s) do our best to provide accurate age and breed of the animal, but sometimes they are educated guesses.  Please understand that statements made regarding this animal are simply overviews and are not guaranteed.  Your adoption fee is non-refundable for any reason.

We are a rescue, and although we have a facility in Modesto most of our dogs/pups are currently being fostered in or around our area. So please be willing to make the trip to see them if you are from out of the area. Our adoption process REQUIRES that an application must first be submitted and approved prior to meeting any of our pets. Just note that we may get several responses on one pet at a time so just because you have an approved application does not mean said pet is on hold for you. One must FIRST confirm an appointment to meet the pet after an approved application has been sent. To inquire about this specific pet, please write to info@pupznpalz.org for an application. Please remember to put the pets name in the subject line when emailing, and on the top on the application. It helps us to help you that must faster. We are a group of volunteers, and ask that you please bare with us. We will get to each person just as quickly as we can. If you do not hear back from us within 24 hours, please send another request as we have been having problems with e-mail.

email: info@pupznpalz.org and ask for an application for which dog you are interested in

phone: 209-480-8662 (9-6 pm only please, cell phone, emergencies only please...do not call to ask status of dog, email please)

**ADOPTION EVENTS: typically every Sat at Modesto Petco 2021 Evergreen Ave from 12-3

**OUR FACILITY: Located at 1430 Carpenter Lane Suite B (by appointment only as we do not have set hours)

animal.description: YOU MUST BE 21 YEARS OF AGE OR OLDER TO ADOPT ABOUT ME: They saved the best for last! I am the last of the Bread Pups and I am ready for my forever homes. I am up to date on my vaccines and I have been neutered. I also have micro chips. I am a puppy and will need regular puppy training and will need a home with a fence. I will need to stay on heart worm prevention and live inside the house. If you would like to meet me please go to www.mobilespca.org and complete an online adoption application and someone will give you a call and set up an appointment. ADOPTION FEE: $250 3 Months 7 Pounds Heart Worm Negative ABOUT OUR PETS: All of our pets available for adoption have been spayed/neutered, tested for heartworms, given age-appropriate vaccinations, microchipped and are on flea and heartworm preventative medication. ADOPTION REQUIREMENTS: To give each dog the best possible home we require a completed Adoption Application. Screening and approval by our Adoption Coordinators and a home visit may be required to make sure this pet fits into your home and the home fits our pet. CONTACT US:If you would like to give this dog a good home please call the Mobile SPCA office at 251-633-3531 or drop by our Adoption Center located at 620 Zeigler Circle W, Mobile, AL 36608 - Tuesday through Friday from 9 a.m. to 5:30 p.m. and Thursday and Saturday from 9 a.m. to 12:00 p.m. CAN'T ADOPT? SPONSOR OR DONATE! This wonderful animal is just one of many in our care right now. Your sponsorship helps us provide shelter, food, and tender loving care for the animals until they find new loving homes. Adoption fees do not cover our expenses, so your sponsorship will make a positive impact on our organization and especially on our animals’ well being. Please note: we are not a chapter or affiliate of any national animal organization. We are, moreover, very grateful for your generosity. Thank you!

animal.breeds_label: Australian Cattle Dog / Blue Heeler & Boxer Mix
animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.Green Arrow came in with his siblings: Phantom and Marvel.

Green Arrow (foster has been calling him Hercules) is a big boy and loves to play with toys and his brother Phantom. He is doing great with potty training, can go up and downstairs, sleeps in a crate with Phantom (they do not whine). When I go to work, they are in the crate for 6 hours and I have not had any issues.

My pack (5 bigger older dogs (3 males and 2 females) have been teaching him manners. He is, a very secure puppy, no anxiety. I have taken him out on a leash and he is learning to walk with me, he is doing good at this and I know he will master it, he loves to be outside. He is a good eater, will sit on couch or floor to nap. He knows the word "NO" and doesn't like it. He is very loving and happy puppy.

His adoption fee is $300 which will include all his age appropriate vaccinations at time of adoption and a neuter that will be scheduled around 4-5 months of age at one of our four vets around the STL area.
